Package com.github.jlgrock.javascriptframework.closuretesting.resultparsing.parsers

The package that holds parsing objects that can create java objects out of the raw google input.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
IDivParser An interface that defines what is necessary for matching a div from the google testing output and parsing it.
 

Class Summary
TestCaseEndParser Parser for the end timing div.
TestCaseFailureStatisticParser The line that reads something like the following: 12 passed, 2 failed.
TestCaseLocationParser Parser for the location.
TestCaseParser The parser for parsed Google Test Case objects.
TestCaseStartParser The start timing div.
TestCaseSummaryParser The object used for parsing the summary.
TestCaseTimingStatisticParser The parser for the object containing timing statistics for the Test Case.
TestFailureStatisticParser The parser for the failure statistic for an individual test.
TestTimingStatisticParser The parsing for the object representing the average time per test that it took to execute the test cases.
